                            <comment id="12656340" author="stack" created="Sat, 13 Dec 2008 21:44:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Bringing into 0.19.0.  We should apply the first patch.  As is, when we do &apos;java -version&apos; into the .log file, that is less than what the runtime jmx bean says as the latter says whats actually running &amp;#8211; &apos;server&apos; vs. &apos;client&apos; or x64 vs. x32.  The emission from &apos;java -version&apos; does not have the command-line args that we actually startup with applied.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
